                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
                <p>Intraduisible.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Not usefully translatable.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p>Intraducibile.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>غير قابل للترجمة بشكل جيد</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>An unclear fragment of a public document engraved amongst a dossier (see <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2000a"/></bibl>). The inventory numbers show that
                    at least some parts of the stone were already in the epigraphic collection at the time of the reorganization of the Cyrenaean antiquities 
                    after World War II care of Goodchild (from 1956 on) and before Fraser observed one of them. In fact for this fragment we now know the circumstances 
                    of the find, see at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr062830</ref>.</p>
	      <p><ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr097600</ref> might be the upper left part of this block: see the commentary there.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
